      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "JAYLA MAGIC (2) produced a moderate performance last time when seventh at Dubbo over 400m behind From The Disco (23.95) in a Grade 4/5. Placed at her previous run. Key runner on her best form. PURE BLUE (4) found trouble in the run here last time and fell and went for a three-and-a-half months spell. Should be in this for a long way. ROYAL BANDIT (6) was strongly supported last start when a short priced favourite and duly saluted winning by a nose at Temora in a handy 19.05. Has a tricky draw to overcome but in form and has the ability. The form from her last run stacks up well. Has hit winning form and can measure up again. CLATTERED (8) won from box 8 last start – cannot be left out of calculations.",
